Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the final session! Virat Kohli gets a guard of honour from the Indian players as he makes his way out to the middle. Dimuth Karunaratne and Lahiru Thirimanne will open the batting for Sri Lanka. Mohammed Shami begins with the ball. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

Sri Lanka will be ruining the fact that they failed to put any pressure on the Indian lower order. They did get wickets on Day 1 despite leaking runs at a brisk rate with top-order Indian batters failing to carry their starts. However, Sri Lanka were pretty flat in the morning session and this afternoon session on Day 2. They failed to put any pressure on Indian batters and the injury to Kumara didn’t help their cause either. There was not much movement for the pacers, Lasith Embuldeniya as well was finding it difficult to turn the ball, which failed to trouble the Indian batters. Overall, it's not been the best effort from Sri Lanka with the ball. Now, they need to step up with the bat, otherwise, things can get even worse for them. The umpires have called for an early Tea! Stay tuned for the final session of Day 2.

India have declared! Over 100 runs in the second session and it's safe to say that another session has belonged to India. They have plenty of runs on the board and the pressure will be on Sri Lanka. It's been a sensational batting performance. We witnessed four Indian batters getting to a solid start yesterday, and none of them went on to make a big total. Pant's blistering knock helped India reach over 350, and today riding on Jadeja's unbeaten 175, along with Ashwin's half-century, India have managed to post 574. They will be hoping to grab some early wickets with the new the help of a new cherry.
Shorter delivery on middle. Shami punches it to long on for a single.  Meanwhile, Rohit Sharma calls his batters in and India declare! India finish with 574/8 in their first innings!
A flatter delivery around leg. Jadeja pulls it to backward square leg for a single.
Dhananjaya de Silva (18-1-77-1) is back into the attack.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja tries to go over cover, but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat towards point. Single taken!
Shami has been hit on his back by the throw from the fielder at the non-striker's end as he completes a quick single. He seems to be in some pain but nothing serious and is ready to resume.

Back of a length, outside off. Mohammed Shami taps it to point and scampers through to the other end. There is a throw at the non-striker's end, but the ball hits Shami on the back. That brings up the 100 run partnership between these two!
Change of pace now! A slower one, angling in on middle, on a length. Ravindra Jadeja eases it to long for a single.
Another length ball, around off. Mohammed Shami looks to push this away but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Edgy runs! Tad fuller, wide of off. Mohammed Shami leans to drive but the ball goes off the outside edge past the second slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, around middle and leg. Ravindra Jadeja works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
TWO LEG BYES! Shorter now, around the pads. Mohammed Shami tries to flick this, but the ball brushes off his pads towards fine leg. Two taken!
Flatter ball now, full in length, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja knocks it to long on for a single.
Loopy ball, very full, around middle and leg. Ravindra Jadeja tucks it towards square leg for a brace.
SIX! Bang! Another fuller ball, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja shimmies down the track and smashes it over long on for a biggie!
Tosses it up, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and defends it out.

FOUR BYES! Nothing is going Sri Lanka's way here! A fuller ball, down the leg side. Ravindra Jadeja looks to sweep but he misses. Niroshan Dickwella too fails to grab the ball, as it sneaks in through his legs towards fine leg for a boundary.
Fuller, around off. Mohammed Shami pushes taps it to mid-off.

Another length delivery, outside off. Mohammed Shami guides it towards cover. The fielder from point slides to stop the ball but fails, another fielder from cover runs for the ball, but he too fails to get hold of the ball. Two taken!
Angling in, on middle. Mohammed Shami tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Mohammed Shami drives and finds the fielder at cover.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Mohammed Shami defends it out solidly.
On a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja taps it towards point for a single.
Touch shorter again, on middle. Mohammed Shami punches it down to long on. Mohammed Shami denies a single a this time.
FOUR! Cut away! Lasith Embuldeniya drops it slightly short, spinning away, outside off. Mohammed Shami slashes it past cover for a boundary.
Quicker and flatter, on middle. Mohammed Shami hangs back and blocks it out.
Down the leg side, touch shorter, Ravindra Jadeja gets low and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Tad shorter, an arm ball, around the pads. Mohammed Shami looks to flick this, but he the ball goes off the outside edge towards point. A single taken!
Loopy ball, fuller, on middle. Mohammed Shami blocks it out.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over! Vishwa Fernando drops it short, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja picks up the length, and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Shami pushes it towards point and takes a single.
A good-length delivery, around off. Shami drives it to mid off.
FOUR! Mohammed Shami adds salt to the wound! A fuller ball, wide of off. Mohammed Shami leans and drives it past cover for a beautiful boundary.

A mix-up...and no harm done! A run out chance but Sri Lanka make a mess of it! An easy opportunity for Sri Lanka. A length ball, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja taps it towards mid-wicket. They run the first one fast, Mohammed Shami comes back for the second, but he is sent back by Ravindra Jadeja mid-way. The fielder though throws it at the wrong end, towards the bowler. Vishwa Fernando too collects the ball and whips the bails off, of the non-striker's end, he did not realize that Shami was well out of his crease. A comedy of errors.
On a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja stays back, opens the face of the bat, and guides it towards third man for a brace.

Drinks! India are in a dominating position and Jadeja is making sure that India get to a position where they can dictate this game completely. India lost Jayant Yadav early in this session but Shami has been solid and is giving good company to his partner. Sri Lanka will be just hoping that India will declare soon but they need to step up and take these two wickets as quickly as possible. Vishwa Fernando (23-1-111-2) is back on.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, around middle. Mohammed Shami pulls it towards fine leg. No run taken!
Suranga Lakmal drops it short now, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja pulls it towards deep square leg. This time Ravindra Jadeja rotates the strike.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja drives it straight to the fielder at deep cover. Another do ball.
Fuller now, spraying it down leg. Ravindra Jadeja clips it towards square leg. No run taken!
Mohammed Shami gets off the mark on his 15th delivery! Length ball, around middle and leg. Mohammed Shami flicks it to fine leg for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Shami blocks it out.
SIX! Ravindra Jadeja brings up his 150 in style! A loopy ball, fuller and around off. Ravindra Jadeja dances down the track and tonks it over long off for a biggie!
No ball and Four! Shorter ball again, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja hangs back and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Dhananjaya de Silva has overstepped here and a no ball is called.

Full again, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja stays in his crease and pushes it on the left of the bowler. Mohammed Shamiwanted a single there, but Ravindra Jadeja says no. Dhananjaya de Silva does well to run to his left and cut the ball out.
Loopy ball, around off. Ravindra Jadeja hangs back and pushes it towards cover.
Slower through the air, full once again, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and defends it out watchfully.
Tosses it up nicely, very full, around off. Ravindra Jadeja pushes it towards mid off.
Loopy ball, full, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja lunges and defends it out.
A full toss this time on middle. Shami plays it down to mid on.
A fuller delivery on middle. Shami blocks it out.

NOT OUT! FOUR LEG BYES! A length delivery on middle and leg. Shami looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a big appeal. The umpire though is not interested. The ball goes towards the off side and the fielder at gully has a shy at the batter's end but misses and the ball goes towards the fence for a boundary as there is no one backing up. In the meanwhile, Sri Lanka have taken a review for LBW. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows umpire's call on wickets hitting. So Shami will continue and India get four leg byes.

Review! Sri Lanka have reviewed an LBW decision against Mohammed Shami. Not bat involved, confirms UltraEdge. Ball Tracker indicates it is the umpire's call on wickets hitting. The on-field decision stands.
NO BALL! Lakmal bangs this one short on off. Jadeja pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single this time. Lakmal has overstepped and the umpire calls it a no ball.
A low full toss on middle. Jadeja flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A fullish delivery on off. Jadeja drives it to mid on.
On a length, around off. Jadeja gets a thick outside edge this time as he looks to defend it. The ball goes towards the gully fielder.
Quicker and flatter delivery on off. Shami defends it back to the bowler.
A flatter delivery on middle. Jadeja works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Another poor delivery and punished by Jadeja! This is slightly short and down the leg side again. Jadeja pulls it towards backward square leg for another boundary.

FOUR! Lasith Embuldeniya overcompensates and serves this short around leg. Jadeja pulls it to backward square leg. The fielder in the deep runs to his left and tries to stop it with a dive but it goes through him for a boundary. 500 up for India!
SIX! Great use of the feet there! A tossed up delivery on middle. Jadeja skips down the track and tonks it straight down the ground for a maximum.
Tossed up on middle. Jadeja blocks this off the front foot.
This time a bit quicker on off. Shami blocks this off the front foot.
Loopy delivery around off. Shami pushes it to covers.
Tad short this time and turning away. It is around off and Jadeja punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Another flighted delivery on off. Jadeja defends it towards the off side.
Beaten this time! Tossed up on middle and there is turn and bounce for Dhananjaya de Silva. It beats the outside edge of Jadeja's blade as he looks to defend.
Tossed up delivery, on off. Jadeja blocks this off the front foot.
Dhananjaya de Silva (16-1-65-1) comes back to bowl.
Another rock-solid defence by Shami! Tossed up nicely on off and equally nicely defended off the front foot by Shami.
Tossed up around off. Shami defends this off the front foot.
A quicker delivery on leg. Jadeja works it towards deep square leg for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Jadeja works it towards the leg side off the back foot this time.
Slower in the air on middle. Jadeja pushes it towards the leg side.
A flatter delivery  on middle. Jadeja blocks it out.
So a single to end the over and Jadeja will retain the strike. A short delivery on middle. Jadeja pulls it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! This time an even better shot! Overpitched on middle. Jadeja drives it straight down the ground for a boundary. The fielder at long on has no chance to stop it.
FOUR! Nicely played this time! Back of a length, around off. Jadeja steers it in the gap towards the third man fence for a boundary.
A fuller delivery on middle. Jadeja flicks it towards cow corner for a couple this time.
A length delivery, around off. Jadeja steers it towards deep point. No single taken again.
A short delivery, around off. Jadeja pulls it firmly to deep mid-wicket but denies a single.
An arm ball this time, quicker and flatter on middle. Shami goes back and defends it comfortably.
A flatter delievry on middle. Shami blocks this off the front foot.
Tossed up around off. Jadeja skips down the track and pushes it to long off for a single.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Jadeja plays it back to the bowler.
On middle this time. Jadeja brings out a reverse-sweep this time and hits it towards the third man region for a couple.
Tossed up delivery, on off. Jadeja blocks it out off the front foot.
Another solid block by Shami! On a length, around off. Shami goes back and defends it.
A good-length delivery, around off. Shami gets right behind it and blocks it.
A full delivery this time on middle. Jadeja flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly shorter delivery and around off. Jadeja looks to pull again but misses.
A length delivery, around off. Jadeja gets forward and defends this.
FOUR! Ohh...lucky for Jadeja! A short delivery around off. Jadeja looks to pull it but gets the inside edge. The ball just goes over the stumps and towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on middle. Shami gets forward and blocks it.
This one is pitched on leg and turning further down the leg side. Jadeja tucks it to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle. Jadeja plays it back to the bowler.
Slower in the air on middle. Jadeja gets well forward and defends it.
Another tossed up delivery on middle. Jadeja knocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller now, loopy ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and blocks it out.
Mohammed Shami walks out to bat.

OUT! TAKEN! Vishwa Fernando is rewarded for his hard work and Jayant Yadav walks back early. Vishwa Fernando was trying to angle the ball across Yadav in the previous deliveries and he does that yet again. He pitches this around off and takes the ball across the batter. Yadav goes for a big booming drive but this time he gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards the first slip fielder and Lahiru Thirimanne takes a good low catch. So eight down now and Sri Lanka will be looking to wrap this up quickly now.
Commentary.Howout: c Lahiru Thirimanne b Vishwa Fernando

Commentary.Commentary: A tad fuller delivery this time, on off. Yadav defends this off the front foot.
A good-length delivery, around off. Yadav defends this watchully towards the off side.
This one is angled across the batter again. It is on a length and outside off. Yadav looks to push at it but misses.
A fuller delivery, outside off. Yadav lets it go this time.

Stifled appeal there but no damage done! A length delivery around off. Jadeja tries to work it towards the off side but the ball hits his pads first and then his bat. The ball goes towards third man for a single.
Who will bowl from the other end? Vishwa Fernando (20-1-94-1) it is!
Slower in the air, on middle. Yadav blocks it out off the front foot.
Another loopy delivery on middle. Yadav pushes it towards the leg side this time.
Tossed up again, on middle stump line. Yadav defends this off the front foot again.
Tossed up delivery, on middle. Yadav gets forward and defends it.
A fuller delivery, outside off. Jadeja pushes it towards point for a single.

Lasith Embuldeniya starts with a flatter delivery around leg. Yadav looks to defend off the front foot. However, he misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards the off side and a leg bye is taken. There is some excitement shown by Sri Lankan players as the ball hit the pad but going down leg.
We are back for the second session! The players are out in the middle. Jayant Yadav and Ravindra Jadeja will resume their batting. Lasith Embuldeniya will begin with the ball. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

Sri Lanka needed this session to go their way but they were quite flat and they never looked like taking a wicket this morning. They are surely hampered by the loss of Lahiru Kumara and their decision to play only one frontline spinner has turned out to be a disaster. The wicket no doubt is good to bat on but Sri Lanka will be mighty disappointed with this session, though there was some respite with Lakmal getting rid of Ashwin at the fag-end of the session. Sri Lanka need some inspiration and better body language in the afternoon session to fight back in this game, otherwise, more misery awaits them. The ploy of bowling short from ‘round the wicket produced a positive result for them at the end and they need more out-of-the-box thinking going forward. The post-Lunch session starts at 12.10 pm IST (6.40 am GMT). Stay tuned.

This session was always going to be crucial in the context of this Test match and the duo of Jadeja-Ashwin have made sure that India are in a dominating position now. Both batters were calm and composed and displayed their worth as genuine all-rounders with chanceless knocks until Ashwin departed trying to take on a short ball. Jadeja reached his second century in Test cricket, a fitting tribute to his mentor and legend, Shane Warne who played a major part in his growth during his Rajasthan days in the Indian T20 league. India generally tends to dominate in home conditions with huge scores in the first innings and the story seems to be continuing in this Test match too. India have scored their runs at a brisk rate so far in this Test and we can expect the same in the afternoon session with Jayant Yadav quite capable of building another partnership with Jadeja.
Shorter again, outside off. Jayant Yadav taps it towards point and scampers through to the other end. That will be Lunch on Day 2!
Back of a length, on middle. Jayant Yadav shows the full face of his bat and defends it out.
On a length, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler, who fails to stop the ball. Single taken!
Shorter ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja watches it sail through to the keeper. Suranga Lakmal has overstepped here and a no ball is given.
Another short delivery, around off. Jadeja ducks under it comfortably.
A short ball angling into the body this time. Jadeja ducks under it.
A full delivery and down the leg side this time. Jadeja lets it go. An official warning has been given to Suranga Lakmal for landing on the danger area.
Tossed up nicely on off. Yadav gets well forward and blocks it.
Very full again, on middle. Jayant Yadav lunges and defends it out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Jayant Yadav defends it out.
Fuller ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja knocks it to long on for a single.
Fuller ball, on middle. Jayant Yadav leans to defend but gets a slight inside edge towards fine leg for a single.

HUNDRED FOR RAVINDRA JADEJA! A shorter ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja cuts it towards deep point for a single. That is his second Test hundred and he is delighted. Out comes his sword and he celebrates with his trademark celebration! He has been pretty consistent with the bat in the last few years and is staying true to the name 'Rockstar' given by the late Shane Warne.
Ends the over with another shorter ball, around middle. Jayant Yadav taps it towards short leg.
Short again, around off. Jayant Yadav defends it out.
Jayant Yadav is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Sri Lanka finally have a breakthrough! Suranga Lakmal has broken this partnerhsip. Ravichandran Ashwin departs after a fine innings! Suranga Lakmal drops it short again, much higher this time, head high. Ravichandran Ashwin goes to pull again, but he manages to get a slight top-edge back to the keeper. Niroshan Dickwella takes an easy catch. Ravichandran Ashwin walks back before the umpire even raises his finger.
Commentary.Howout: c Niroshan Dickwella b Suranga Lakmal

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Nicely done! Fraction short, on the body. Ravichandran Ashwin pullls this towards deep mid-wicket. It does not go off the middle of the bat, but the ball will race away towards the fence for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin stays in his crease and taps it to cover.
Shorter ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single. Ravindra Jadeja on 99 now.
Very full again, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja eases it down to long on for a single. He moves on to 98 and he will keep strike for the next over!

FOUR! Runs are flowing for India at the moment! Another gorgeous drive. Lasith Embuldeniya serves a half-volley this time, around off, loopy delivery as well. Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and creams it past cover for a boundary. He moves to 97 with that!
Tosses it up, full and around off. Ravindra Jadeja lunges and blocks it out.
Pitches it up, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja drills it towards the right of the bowler, who dives and makes good stop
Loopy ball, outside off, fuller in length. Ravindra Jadeja leans and leaves it alone.
Very full, on middle, slower through the air. Ravichandran Ashwin works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter ball, down the leg side. Ravindra Jadeja taps it towards the vacant square leg region for a brace. 450 up for India!
On a length, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin chops it onto the ground, over the fielder at gully for a single.
Fraction shorter now, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja cuts it towards deep point and rotates the strike.
This one lands on a length, outside off again. Ravindra Jadeja taps it towards the fielder at cover.
Good-length delivery, around off. Ravindra Jadeja leans and tries to block it, but gets an inside edge back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja stays back and cuts it towards the fielder at gully.
Suranga Lakmal (20-1-74-1) is back into the attack.
Flatter now, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin defends it out. A maiden over! First of the day!
around off, full again. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it towards mid off.
Full again, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin shows the full face of his bat and defends it out.
Flighted ball, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin presses forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
Another loopy ball, outside off, full in length. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it out.
Tosses it up, outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and defends it towards the fielder at cover.
Outside off, fuller in length. Ravichandran Ashwin opens the face of his bat and pushes it towards point for a single.
Loopy ball, full and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and blocks it out solidly.
FOUR! Glorious! Very full, outside off, slower through the air again. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and drives it beautifully past cover for a gorgeous boundary.
Fuller ball, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it out.
Turning it away, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja chops it towards point for a single.

Short in length, around middle, this one stays low as well. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it towards cover for a single. Fifty for Ravichandran Ashwin! He has looked so composed! Good half-century from him!
Short, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja defends it out.
Shorter this time, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja cuts it off the back foot towards deep cover. The fielder runs to his left, dives, and makes a good stop. Two taken!
Loopy ball, full in length, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and tucks it towards square leg for a single.

FOUR! Exquisite timing! He has made it look so easy! Very full, slower through the air, around middle and leg. Ravichandran Ashwin shimmies down the pitch and pushes it gently past mid on for a boundary.
Fuller, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball, outside off, on a fuller length. Ravindra Jadeja leans, opens the face of his bat, and pushes it towards point. Single taken!
Fuller this time, tosses it up on this occasion, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and blocks it out towards the mid-wicket region.
Flatter ball, around middle and leg. Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, very full again, Ravindra Jadeja drives it with the inner half of his bat past mid on for a single. That brings up the 100-run stand between these two!
Very full, loopy ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja blocks it out towards the off side.
Loopy ball, full, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja drives it to the fielder at short cover.
Spinning it in, outside off, touch shorter this time. Ravindra Jadeja cuts it off the back foot towards deep point for a single. He retains the strike!
Flighted delivery, full in length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja lunges and tries to block but the ball goes off the outside edge towards third man. Two runs taken!
Tosses it up, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja presses forward, drives, and finds the fielder at cover.
Slower through the air, outside off, on a fuller length. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and drives it towards deep cover. Single taken!
Lasith Embuldeniya goes 'round the wicket, serves a loopy ball, full, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and defends it out.
Turning it in, outside off, tad shorter. Ravindra Jadeja rocks back and pushes it towards sweeper cover for a single.
Lasith Embuldeniya (34-2-130-2) is back into the attack. The loss of Lahiru Kumara is really hurting Sri Lanka. They need some inspiration from somewhere and Lasith Embuldeniya need to step up here.
Full, around middle and leg. Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it off the back foot towards deep square leg. Two taken!
Fullish delivery again, around middle. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and tucks it to square leg. Another dot ball.
Fuller ball, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and defends it out.
Flighted again, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, full and on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin leans and taps it to the fielder at mid-wicket.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Very full on this occasion, around off. Ravichandran Ashwin presents the full face of the bat and drives it past mid off for a boundary. He moves on to 41 with that!
Fraction shorter, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin stays in his crease and defends it towards cover.
On a length, wide of off. Ravindra Jadeja hangs back and cuts it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin guides towards deep point for a single.
Good-length delivery, wide of off. Ravindra Jadeja slashes it towards past point. Single taken!
On a length, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin stays back and pushes it towards deep cover and rotates the strike.

Slower in the air, on middle. Ashwin drives it back to the bowler.

Quicker delivery on middle. Ashwin gets forward and defends it towards the leg side.
Tossed up nicely on off. Jadeja drives it to long off for a single.

DRINKS! Ravindra Jadeja and Ravichandran Ashwin are looking quite comfortable at the crease. They have been scoring runs and have not the let the bowlers trouble them. The duo has put 79 runs together and will be looking to carry on the same way till Lunch. Sri Lanka have been wicketless so far, and they will have to break this partnership and not let India get away with a bigger total.
A length delivery, outside off. Ashwin pushes it to covers this time.
A length delivery, around off and a bit of extra bounce this time. Ashwin defends this but takes his hands off the handle as the ball hits high on the bat.
A length delivery and wider outside off. Ashwin leaves it alone.
FOUR! What a shot! This is full outside off. Ashwin leans forward and plays a lovely cover-drive as the ball races away towards the fence in a flash.

Fuller delivery on middle. Jadeja drives it to mid on for a quick single.

A slightly shorter delivery, around off. Ashwin punches it to covers for a single.
Flatter and on off. Ashwin blocks it out this time.

The action is all set to begin on Day 2! This first hour will be crucial with a new cherry of just five overs old at Sri Lanka's disposal. Both teams are wearing black bands and served a minute of silence in the memory of the late Shane Warne earlier. The Sri Lankan players are out there in the middle. Ravindra Jadeja and Ravichandran Ashwin are into the middle as well to resume their innings. Lasith Embuldeniya to start with the ball for Sri Lanka. Here we go...

PITCH REPORT - Deep Dasgupta and Ajit Agarkar are near the pitch. Ajit Agarkar says it still looks like a batting wicket, there are bare pitches and we can still expect some turn. Mentions that a little bit wear and tear on Day 2 and Sri Lanka will only find it tough to bat on. Deep Dasgupta adds that the pitch is only going to start favouring the spinners.

As we build towards Day 2 of this Test match it is worth mentioning that the cricketing world will be poorer with the shocking news of the passing away of legendary leg-spinner Shane Warne due to a suspected heart attack in Thailand on March 4, 2022. Warney was a legend and once in a century player in a true sense, his artistry with the ball mesmerized generations of young kids around the world and with 708 Test wickets, he showed the world that conditions doesn’t matter if you have class and skills to exceed. He has been a superstar and a torch-bearer of the art of leg-spin and cricket as a whole and the cricketing world will never be the same without him.

The first day of this Test match turned out to be quite an absorbing one with pitch assisting both bowlers and batters, the competition was quite even between the two sides. India did score runs at a brisk rate but kept losing wickets and that ensured that Sri Lanka were always in the game. However, Pant’s counter-attacking knock tilted the day in India’s favour and with still some batting to go, India will be looking to put a big score on the board on Day 2. The first session holds the key for both these teams and we might see some intense and quality action along the way. An interesting first session coming up. Stay tuned.

Hanuma Vihari is down for a chat. He says that he felt good going out in the middle, he enjoyed his time and he feels good to grab this opportunity of batting at number 3. Mentions that if the team requires him to bat at a different position he will be happy to do it, but his preferred position is to bat at number 3. States that initially the ball was coming on nicely to the bat but once the ball got old, it got tougher, but Rishabh is a different player altogether as he made it look easy. Informs that Pant's innings was special and helped them get to 350 on Day 1.

This is only the first day of the Test match but it is quite evident that Sri Lanka have made a mistake by going with just one frontline spinner. The injury to Kumara have made things worse for them, however, they have still managed to pick six wickets and have not let the game drift away completely for them. Lasith Embuldeniya was the pick of the bowlers as he bowled with great accuracy and clever change of pace but Pant was brutal towards him in the final session. It is still a decent day for Lanka and if they can pick the remaining wickets quickly on Day 2, we have an interesting Day 2 ahead of us. The pitch though is perfect for Test cricket with help for both seamers and spinners and there is value for shots as well for the batters.

Rishabh Pant unleashed all his might in the final session and despite India losing the wicket of Iyer, Pant made sure that all the pressure was on Lankans for the most part of the final session. He took Lasith Embuldeniya and Dhananjaya de Silva to the cleaners and that forced the Lankan skipper to bring his pacers back. However, the new ball brought some respite for Lankans as Pant missed out on a well-deserved century. The pair of Jadeja and Ashwin made sure that there are no more setbacks and with Jayant Yadav to follow, India will be looking to cross 400 on Day 2. However, India would have been in a much better situation if one of their batters would have carried on after getting the desired starts as the pitch seems quite good to bat on.

What an engrossing day of Test cricket! Every time, India seems to be going ahead quite comfortably, Sri Lanka have made found a way back into this game with a wicket. However, India have scored at quite a decent rate and that has made sure that despite them losing six wickets, India will go back as the happier side at the end of Day 1.
