Short in length, spinning away, outside off. Rishabh Pant pushes it towards deep cover for a single.
Tad quicker and flatter, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja hangs back and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and on middle. Ravindra Jadeja defends it out.
Much slower through the air now, full and on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and blocks it out.
Shorter and quicker, around middle and off. Rishabh Pant cuts it towards point for a single.
FOUR! Clever shot! A fuller ball, loopy one, around the leg pole. Rishabh Pant gets down on his knee and scoops it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Shorter ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja slashes it towards cover for a single.
Shorter ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja knocks it towards mid on for a single. He retains the strike.
Tosses it up, full, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja defends it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja leans and taps it to point.
Quicker, around middle and leg. Ravindra Jadeja pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and defends it out.
Shorter ball, around middle. Ravindra Jadeja knocks it to the fielder at mid on.
Fuller again, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja eases it down to long on for a single.
Shorter and quicker, around middle and leg. Ravindra Jadeja blocks it out off the back foot.
Another loopy ball, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and defends it out.
Slower through the air, full, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and blocks it out.
A fuller delivery on off. Pant skips down the track and pushes it to long off for a single.
FOUR! Good shot by Pant! Slightly shorter outside off this time. Pant cuts it through point for a boundary. Nice shot beats the diving fielder at backward point comfortably.
Tosses it up, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja defends it out.
Shorter, on the pads. Ravindra Jadeja pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Full again, loopy ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja defends it out.
Beauty! Slower through the air, full again, spinning away outside off. Ravindra Jadeja leans to block but misses.
Fuller ball, on middle. Ravindra Jadeja leans and defends it out.
Ravindra Jadeja is the next man in.

Review! Shreyas Iyer has been given out LBW here! He has taken a review straightaway! He is in trouble if he has not got bat on this one. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows three reds, so Shreyas Iyer has to walk back.

OUT! LBW! Dhananjaya de Silva comes back into the attack and strikes on his first ball! He picks up the wicket of Shreyas Iyer! A peach of a delivery! A fuller ball, turning it in on middle. Shreyas Iyer looks to defend this but gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball spins back into him and hits him on the back pad. The umpire raises his finger immediately after the appeal. Shreyas Iyer opts for a review! No bat involved confirms UltraEdge. Three reds indicated Ball Tracker! Shreyas Iyer has to depart and India lose a review as well.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Dhananjaya de Silva

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller ball, around middle and leg. Rishabh Pant pushes it towards mid-wicket.

Lahiru Kumara is walking off the field! This is not a good news from Sri Lankan point of view. There seems to be some kind of niggle but doesn't looks that serious as he was walking off quite comfortably off the field. Kusal Mendis is the substitute fielder replacing him. Let's hope that Lahiru Kumara will be back on the field pretty soon.
Much fuller now, down the leg side on this occasion. Rishabh Pant tries to flick but misses.
Another length delivery, outside off, at 133.4 clicks. Rishabh Pant opens the face of the bat and guides it past point for a brace.
Good-length delivery, around the off pole. Rishabh Pant leans and defends it out.
Fraction shorter, on middle. Rishabh Pant shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.
A length ball, wide of off. Rishabh Pant stays in his crease and slashes it towards deep cover for a brace. That brings up the 50-run stand between these two!
Another one on that middle and leg line. Iyer is well forward to block it again.
Goes over the wicket now and serves this on middle and leg. Iyer defends this off the front foot.
A flatter delivery on middle and coming through with the arm at 83.6 kph. Iyer works it towards the leg side.
A slightly shorter delivery on middle. A natraj pull-shot by Pant this time to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slower in the air around leg. Iyer works it to mid-wicket for a single. Iyer looks for a second run there but Pant sends him back.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Iyer gets well forward and blocks it.
A good-length delivery, around off. Iyer looks to defend it but the ball catches the inside edge of his blade. It goes past stumps behind square on the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Lovely timing by Iyer! A fullish delivery that is drifting on the pads. Iyer uses his wrists and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
A good-length delivery, on off at 138.2 kph. Iyer opens the face of his blade and hits it to point.
Another short delivery, on off. Not very high this time and Pant pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
A good bouncer this time on off at 141.1 kph. Pant sways away from the line of the ball.
A length delivery, around off. Pant blocks it out towards the off side.
Loopy delivery, on off. Iyer nicely defends this off the front foot again.
Slower in the air, on off. Iyer gets right forward to block it.
Slightly shorter delivery on middle this time. Pant goes deep in his crease and pulls it in his own unusual fashion towards deep backward square leg for a single.
This is interesting! Another loopy delivery on middle. Pant advances again but is nowhere near the pitch off the ball and blocks it out.
Tossed up on middle this time. Pant skips down the track but ends up just defending it.
FOUR! A rare bad delivery by Lasith Embuldeniya! A flatter delivery turning into leg. Pant clips it fine towards long leg for a boundary.
This one holds on the surface a little bit! On a length, around off. Iyer plays it a tad early and checks his shot but plays it quite well in the end.
Another delivery, on that good length and around off. Iyer defends it towards the off side.
A length delivery, outside off. Iyer pushes it towards the off side now.
A length delivery, on off. Iyer watches it carefully and blocks it out.
FOUR! This time he decides to not back away from his natural instinct! A fullish delivery, around off. Iyer goes with the flow and drives it uppishly over covers for a boundary.
On a good length, around off. Probably coming into Iyer a little this time. He looks to drive it towards the off side but gets the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Goes slower and fuller on off. Pant takes a step or two well forward and defends it nicely.
This is outside off. Iyer pushes it towards point and takes a single.
Goes shorter on middle. Pant uses the depth of the crease and works it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Quicker this time on off at 89.2 kph. Pant defends this off the front foot.
Slightly shorter on off. Iyer goes back and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Iyer defends it towards short leg.
Hits that length hard again, on off. Pant gets forward and defends it towards the off side.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Pant leaves it alone.
FOUR! Typical Rishabh Pant! A length deliver, outside off. Pant skips down the track and makes room for himself. He hits this over the cover fielder for a boundary.
First run of the final session, and with that, the 200 comes up for India! A fullish delivery, outside off. Iyer drives it towards deep point for a single.
Goes slightly shorter this time, on off. Iyer goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Lakmal starts with a full delivery, on off. Iyer drives it to mid off.
Suranga Lakmal will bowl from the other end.
Quicker again, around off. Pant pushes it towards the off side. A maiden to start the session.
Slightly shorter on middle and turning into Pant. He looks to work it away but gets hit high on the pads.
Goes fuller this time, on off. Pant flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter again, on middle. Pant pushes it left of the bowler.
A flatter and slightly shorter delivery on off. Pant goes back and blocks it.
Tossed up around off. Pant gets well forward and defends it. Very slow in the air to start this session by Lasith Embuldeniya.
We are back for the final session! The players are out in the middle. Shreyas Iyer and Rishabh Pant will resume the batting for India. Lasith Embuldeniya will begin with the ball. Here we go...
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

Like the first session, India have lost two wickets in this session as well. They were cruising along nicely in the first hour of the session, but both Hanuma Vihari and Virat Kohli perished soon and failed to make it big. Hanuma Vihari did play a fine knock of 58 after being promoted to number 3.  All the four batters got to a good start but they failed to go big. Shreyas Iyer and Rishabh Pant are currently at the crease and building a partnership. India will be hoping they go on and put a healthy total on the board. India are still in the driver's seat for now. Let's see how the third session pans out. Stay tuned! The third session will begin at 2:30 pm IST (9:00 am GMT).

A much better session for Sri Lanka! A good display of bowling from them in this session and they will be mighty pleased with their effort. They did not let the batters score freely this time and got rid of two set batters, Hanuma Vihari and Virat Kohli. Lasith Embuldeniya once again was the stand-out bowler, as he got the big wicket of Kohli and kept things tight as well. The only thing Sri Lanka will be disappointed with would be about the no balls. They will look to minimize those in the final session.
Another delivery on that tight line, on off. Iyer gets well forward and negotiates it safely. At Tea on Day 1, India are 199/4!
A length delivery, around off. Iyer drives it on up towards the cover fielder.
Bit fuller and around off. Iyer drives it to covers this time.
A length delivery angling into middle this time. Iyer pushes it towards the leg side.
This time a length delivery, on off. Iyer blocks it out.
FOUR! Glorious shot! A fullish delivery, around off. Iyer leans forward and drives it. He opens the face of his blade a little and gets it wide of deep extra-cover fielder for a boundary.
Slower in the air, on off. Pant gets well forward and blocks it.
Tossed up around off. Pant defends this towards the off side with soft hands.
A fuller delivery, on off. Iyer pushes it to covers for a single.

Edge this time but the ball falls short of the first slip fielder! A tossed up delivery on middle. There is drift and turn this time and the ball catches the outside edge of Iyer's blade as he looks to defend. The ball falls short of Lahiru Thirimanne at first slip and Iyer survives.
Slightly quicker at 83.9 kph on middle. Iyer defends this again off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Iyer gets well forward and defends it.
Pulls his length back this time, around off. Pant rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Slightly fuller on middle. Iyer glances it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length and angling into middle and leg at 126.7 kph. Iyer defends this comfortably towards the off side.
This time a quick single! A length delivery around off. Pant pushes it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a single.
A length delivery, around off and angling across Pant. He defends this off the front foot afain.
A good-length delivery, on off. Pant defends it towards the off side.
Quicker now, an arm ball, tad shorter, on middle. Shreyas Iyer stays back and misses his flick.
Fuller ball, outside off, tosses it up on this occasion. Shreyas Iyer leans and chips it towards cover. Dimuth Karunaratne dives it to his right and collects it on the bounce.
Tad shorter, around middle. Shreyas Iyer goes back and flicks with the inner half of his bat towards square leg for a single.
Tad quicker, around middle. Rishabh Pant rocks back and whips it towards deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, on middle. Pant leans and defends it out.
Shorter ball, turning it away, outside off. Shreyas Iyer stays back and pushes it towards cover. Single taken!
Another length delivery, outside off. Rishabh Pant looks to block this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one lands on a length, outside off. Rishabh Pant shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Shreyas Iyer hangs back and pushes it towards deep cover and rotates the strike.
Another length delivery, outside off. Shreyas Iyer cuts it towards deep point. Two taken!
Another length delivery, outside off, at 135.1 clicks. Shreyas Iyer does not fiddle with it.
On a length, outside off. Shreyas Iyer leaves it alone.
Shorter ball, around middle. Shreyas Iyer pushes it towards square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, full, on middle. Rishabh Pant steps down the pitch again and knocks it past mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off, turning it away from the right-hander, Shreyas Iyer dabs it towards point for a single.
Tad shorter, turning it in, around middle. Rishabh Pant steps advances down the pitch and pushes it towards long on for a single.
SIX! Bangs! First six of the innings! Fuller ball, turning it in, around middle. Rishabh Pant steps down and tonks it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie!
Fuller ball, spinning it in, on middle. Rishabh Pant defends it out.
Full in length, outside off, at 128.1 clicks. Shreyas Iyer lets that go through. End of another successful over for Sri Lanka!
Fullish ball again, shaping away outside off. Shreyas Iyer offers no shot.
Pitches it up, outside off, shaping away. Shreyas Iyer leaves it alone.
Shreyas Iyer walks in at number 6.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Vishwa Fernando strikes this time! He gets rid of another set batter. Hanuma Vihari departs after a fine innings! Fuller ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leans and looks to drive this, but the ball goes off the inside edge of his blade and knocks the leg stump over! Just want Sri Lanka needed. Two new batters at the crease now.
Commentary.Howout: b Vishwa Fernando

Commentary.Commentary: Very full, outside off again. Hanuma Vihari pushes it to the fielder at point.
Length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it out.
Vishwa Fernando will continue.
Tosses it up, on middle and off, full in length. Hanuma Vihari eases it to long off for a single.
No ball! Fuller ball again, slower through the air again, on middle. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it out. Lasith Embuldeniya has overstepped once again and a no ball is given!
Much slower through this time, outside off, loopy ball. Hanuma Vihari presses forward and defends it out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out.
Tosses it up, full and around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it out.
Full again, on middle. Hanuma Vihari taps it towards square leg off the back foot.
Loopy ball, fuller again, outside off. Hanuma Vihari lunges and defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Rishabh Pant cuts it onto the ground and the ball flies over the fielder at gully. Two taken!
Back of a length, shaping back in, around the fifth stump line. Rishabh Pant shoulders his arms at it.
Angling into the left-hander, on a length, outside off. Rishabh Pant offers no shot to that.
This one lands on a length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari slashes it towards deep point for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Hanuma Vihari shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Shorter now, turning it into the left-hander. Rishabh Pant stays in his crease and pushes it towards mid-wicket. An excellent over from Lasith Embuldeniya!
SLower through the air, full again on middle. Rishabh Pant pushes it uppishly towards the bowler. The ball falls just short of Lasith Embuldeniya.
A loopy ball, fuller, around middle. Rishabh Pant steps down and pushes it back to the bowler.
Rishabh Pant walks in at number 5.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! That's a huge, huge wicket! Change of ends for Lasith Embuldeniya has worked for Sri Lanka! Lasith Embuldeniya strikes once again and sends back Virat Kohli this time. A fuller ball, this one lands around middle and turns away towards the off pole. Virat Kohli rocks back and tries to defend this, but he gets beaten past the outside edge as the ball spins away from him and knocks the off stump. India lose their third wicket.
Commentary.Howout: b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: Flighted delivery, full and outside off. Virat Kohli leans and blocks it out.
Slower through the air, full in length, on middle. Virat Kohli leans and pushes it towards mid on.
Good-length delivery, around off. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out.
On a length again, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Another length delivery, outside off. Hanuma Vihari defends it out.

No ball! Full ball, wide of off. Hanuma Vihari drives it uppishly away from his towards Dhananjaya de Silva at point, who drops the catch. Lucky for him, Vishwa Fernando has overstepped has a no ball is called! That is the 7th no ball of the innings.
Length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli taps it towards point for a single.
FOUR! Wow, wonderful shot! Very full, wide of off. Virat Kohli presses forward, reaches out to it, and creams it past cover for a beautiful boundary. He moves to 40 now!
On a length, around middle. Virat Kohli defends it out.
Shorter one again, outside off. Hanuma Vihari stays in his crease and pushes it past first slip for a brace.
Back of a length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari stays back and dabs it towards point.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Hanuma Vihari drives and finds the fielder at cover.
Pitches it up again, outside off. Hanuma Vihari blocks it towards point.
Tosses it up again, outside off, on a fuller length. Hanuma Vihari presses forward and blocks it out.
Loopy ball, full, around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it out.

Drinks! This partnership is going along quite nicely and India are in a position of strength now. Both the batters are looking quite comfortable in the middle and apart from Lasith Embuldeniya, Sri Lankan bowers are not threatening these two batters enough to produce some positive result for the Lankans. They need to break this partnership quickly otherwise a big first innings score is right on the cards!
Another length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
Another length ball, wide of off. Hanuma Vihari stays in his crease and slashes it towards deep point. the fielder there runs across to his right and cuts it out. Single taken!
Length ball, width on offer. Virat Kohli pushes it towards deep cover for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 136.7 clicks. Virat Kohli watches it sail through to the keeper.
Tad fuller, wide of off this time. Virat Kohli offers no shot to that.
Back of a length, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
Another delivery that is slower in the air, on off. Vihari defends this off the front foot again.
Tossed up around off. Vihari get well forward and blocks it.
A fullish delivery on off. Kohli drives it to long off for a single.
Quicker delivery on middle. Kohli works it towards the leg side.
Ohh...in the air for a while! A slighlty shorter delivery on off and this one holds on the surface a bit and Kohli pushes it a tad early. The ball goes in the air but falls short of the bowler.
NO NALL!  Third no ball by the spinner! A fuller delivery, around off. Kohli pushes it towards the off side as Lasith Embuldeniya oversteps again.
Tossed up on middle. Kohli gets well forward and defends it.
Change of ends for Lasith Embuldeniya!
A good-length delivery, around off. Vihari watches it till the end and lets it go.
Another harmless length delivery, outside off. Vihari leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Vihari lets it go this time.
On a length, around off. Vihari blocks it out calmly as ever.

8000 Test runs for Kohli in his 100th Test match! What a tremendous achievement by a tremendous player! 6th Indian to reach the landmark! A length delivery, outside off. Kohli pushes it to deep cover for a single.
A slightly shorter delivery, way outside off from 'round the wicket. Kohli leaves it alone.
Vishwa Fernando (5-0-35-0) comes back into the attack.
A length delivery, around off at 142.6 kph. Vihari is solid in his defence. India are going along nicely here.
On a length, around off at 138 kph. Kohli pushes it towards the off side for a single.
Kumara goes back of a length again, outside off. Vihari pushes it towards deep point for a single again.
Back of a length, outside off. Kohli punches it to deep cover for a single.
On a length, on off. Kohli gets forward and blocks it out.
FOUR! SHOT! Short and width provided this time. Kohli cuts it to through covers for a boundary. More of a back foot punch this, plays it well in front of square.
Slower in the air, on off. Kohli drives it towards the off side and takes a single. 150 up for India! Lasith Embuldeniya has been bowling non-stop from one end, will we see him bowling another over?
Quicker and fuller on middle. Vihari pushes it to mid on for a single.
Nicely tossed up on off at 82 kph. Vihari gets well forward and blocks it towards the off side.
Fuller and on middle again. Kohli works it right of mid on and takes a quick single.
Loopy delivery on middle. Kohli works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off. Vihari drives it to long off for a single.

Fifty for Hanuma Vihari! He has been given the opportunity to bat at number 3 today and he has grabbed it with both hands. A shorter delivery on middle. Vihari pulls it to fine leg for a single. He would like to get a big one here!
On a length, on middle. Kohli works it to deep square leg for a single.
Kumara bangs this short around leg. Kohli looks to pull but misses. The ball goes just past his gloves there.
On a length, on off. Vihari works it towards the leg side for a single. A bit of reverse swing there!
Back of a length, on off. Vihari punches this off the back foot towards the off side.
A short delivery and down the leg side. Vihari looks to pull it but misses.
Quicker and around leg. Kohli looks to work it towards the leg side but misses and the ball hits his pads. However, it is going down leg.
Goes fuller on off. Vihari drives it to long off for a single.
Pulls his length back a little and pushes this one a tad quicker on middle and leg. Vihari defends it towards the leg side.
Another loopy delivery on middle. Vihari gets well forward and blocks it out.
Slightly slower on middle. Vihari defends it towards the leg side.
On middle and fuller at 84.4 kph. Vihari drives it back to the bowler.
Goes a bit more fuller this time on off at 141.1 kph. Kohli drives it to mid on.
A good-length delivery around off. Kohli gets forward and blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Vihari rides the bounce and punches it to deep cover for a single.
This is short and wider outside off. Kohli cuts it to deep point for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Kohli decides to leave it alone. This is the line you need to bowl to Kohli.
Back of a length, on off. Vihari punches it to covers for a single.
Lahiru Kumara (6-1-29-1) is back on!
Another tossed up delivery on off. Kohli defends this off the front foot.
He goes fuller this time and slower in the air on off. Kohli gets well forward now to block it.
Another delivery on the shorter side on off. Kohli is solid in his defence again.
Quicker and fatter on off. Kohli goes back and blocks it out.
NO BALL! Fuller on off. Vihari drives it to deep cover for a single. Lasith Embuldeniya has overstpped again and this is poor from the spinner.
Slower in the air on off. Vihari gets forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Kohli drives it left of the bowler. Lasith Embuldeniya dives to stop it but ends up deflecting it towards the mid off region for a single.
On a length, around off and this one nips back in. Kohli looks to push it towards the off side but gets the inside edge behind square on the leg side for a single.
Goes fuller this time on off. Kohli looks to drive it towards the off side but the ball hits the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
This time a shorter length delivery on off at 124 kph. Vihari pulls it to fine leg for a single.
A length delivery and shapinng into Vihari a little. Vihari gets forward and defends it.
Back of a length, around off. Virat Kohli stays back and pushes it towards cover-point for a single.
A length delivery on off. Kohli blocks it out.
Nicely bowled this time. Loopy delivery around off. Vihari presses forward to defend but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade. It goes through the third man region for a couple.
NO BALL! A fuller delivery, outside off. Kohli drives it to deep cover for a single. Lasith Embuldeniya has overstepped and the umpire calls it a no ball!

FOUR! Short and Kohli uses the depth of the crease to a great effect! Lasith Embuldeniya has been bowling short in this over and ends up bowling another short delivery on off. Kohli goes back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up this around off. Kohli gets forward and defends it.
Quicker and flatter on off. Kohli blocks this off the back foot.
Around off and turning away a little. Kohli goes back and punches it back to the bowler.
A flatter and shorter delivery, around off. Vihari cuts it to deep cover for a single.
Back of a length, around middle. Hanuma Vihari stays in his crease and looks to block this, but the ball goes off the outside edge past point for a single.
Fullish delivery now, touch wider of the off stump. Hanuma Vihari does not fiddle with that.
On a length now, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leans and leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off, at 130.0 clicks. Hanuma Vihari lets that go through to the keeper.
NO BALL! Length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari offers no shot on that. Suranga Lakmal has overstepped and the umpire signals a no ball.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Perfect timing on that one. A length ball, angling in on the pads. Hanuma Vihari flicks it past mid on for a glorious boundary.
On a length, shaping in, around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it out.
Very full, on middle, flighted ball. Virat Kohli knocks it towards mid off.
Loopy ball, around off, full in length. Virat Kohli lunges and defends it out.
Flatter and an arm ball, on middle. Hanuma Vihari pushes it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tosses it up, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leans and leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, fuller again. Hanuma Vihari leans and blocks it out.
Slower through the air, spinning away, around off. Hanuma Vihari stays back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, coming back in, outside off. Virat Kohli leaves it alone.
Outside off now, on a length. Virat Kohli blocks it out.

An appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! Length ball, angling in on the pads again. Virat Kohli shuffles across and tries to flick this but misses and gets hit on the pads. That was sliding down leg.
FOUR! Top shot! Tadd fuller, angling in on the pads. Virat Kohli waits for it, uses his wrists and flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length again, jagging back in, around middle. Virat Kohli taps it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, angling in, outside off. Virat Kohli shoulders his arms.
Suranga Lakmal will start from the other end. So Sri Lanka opting for the combination of spin-pace after Lunch.
Flighted delivery, full in length, around off. Hanuma Vihari lunges and blocks it out solidly.
Fuller again, around middle and leg. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out towards the leg side.
Tosses it up again, full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari presses forward and blocks it out.
Another flighted delivery, fuller again, on middle. Hanuma Vihari defends it out off the front foot.
Tosses it up, full, on middle. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out.
FOUR! Hanuma Vihari begins the post-Lunch session with a boundary! Very full, loopy, on middle. Hanuma Vihari drills it past mid on for a boundary.

We are back for the middle session! Sri Lankan players are out there in the middle. Hanuma Vihari and Virat Kohli also walk out to resume their innings. Lasith Embuldeniya to start with the ball for Sri Lanka. Hanuma Vihari will be on strike. Here we go...
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 …

The pitch had little help for the seam bowlers at the start but Vishwa Fernando failed to bowl at consistent lines and lengths. Lakmal though was quite good but it was the extra pace of Kumara that brought them their first breakthrough as Kumara got rid of dangerous Rohit Sharma. However, the star of this session for Sri Lanka was Lasith Embuldeniya who bowled with great control and his change of pace troubled almost all Indian batters. He got the set Agarwal and it will be interesting to see how he and Dhananjaya de Silva bowl in the afternoon session. Remember, they are playing just one frontline spinner with Dhananjaya de Silva, the spinning all-rounder. The afternoon session is expected to be as absorbing as this one if not more so stay tuned as the post-Lunch session resumes at 12.10 pm IST (6.40 am GMT).

The first session of any Test match is very crucial and we can safely say that both teams will be quite happy with their effort in this session. India started off in a positive fashion as Rohit and Mayank went about their business in quite a confident manner. However, Rohit departed just when he was looking ominous for Sri Lanka and then his opening partner Agarwal also could not build on the start he got. India’s new number 3, Vihari and the man playing his 100th Test, Virat Kohli ensured that there are no further damages and overall India will be quite happy with their scoring-rate in this session.

Shorter one now, on middle. Virat Kohli punches it down to long on and runs across to the other end. The fielder there throws it towards the bowler's end, and there is no back up there. An overthrow taken! That will be lunch on Day 1!
Loopy ball, full, on middle. Hanuma Vihari eases it down to long on for a single.
Flatter and fuller, around middle. Virat Kohli tucks it towards mid-wicket. A misfield there allows them to take a single.
Tad shorter, turning it in, on middle. Virat Kohli stays in his crease and defends it out.
Tosses it up, on middle. Virat Kohli pushes it back to the bowler.
Dhananjaya de Silva goes over the wicket now, serves a loopy ball, full in length, around middle. Virat Kohli defends it out.
Another flighted delivery, outside off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, fuller, outside off. Hanuma Vihari presses forward and blocks it out.
Flighted delivery again, around middle and leg. Hanuma Vihari tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter one now, full, on middle. Hanuma Vihari stays back and blocks it out.
Loopy ball, full and outside off. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out.
Tosses it up, very full, on middle. Virat Kohli pushes it towards deep square leg for three runs.
Floated delivery, fuller ball, around middle. Hanuma Vihari pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, fuller ball. Hanuma Vihari defends it out.
Tosses it up again, on middle, on a fuller length. Hanuma Vihari blocks it out.
Loopy ball, fuller, around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and defends it out.
Fuller now, flatter. Virat Kohli knocks it towards long on for a single.
Shorter ball, outside off. Virat Kohli taps it towards mid off.
Floated delivery, fuller, outside off. Virat Kohli taps it towards point for a single. He retains the strike!
Tosses it up, around off, full in length. Virat Kohli lunges and defends.
Another fuller ball, slower through the air again, around middle. Virat Kohli presses forward and defends it out.
Loopy ball, full again, around off. Virat Kohli leans and blocks it out solidly.
Fuller now, around middle. Virat Kohli tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Shorter now, spinning away, outside off. Hanuma Vihari, on the back foot pushes it towards deep cover for a single. That brings up the 100 for India!
Length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari pushes it off the back foot towards point for a single. He will keep strike for the next over!
Tad shorter, outside off. Virat Kohli taps it towards point and rotates the strike!
Back of a length, on middle. Virat Kohli stays in his crease and defends it out.
Another length ball, outside off. Virat Kohli blocks it towards cover.
FOUR! A straight drive cannot get better than that! Very full, around off. Virat Kohli presents the full face of the bat and drives it past the bowler for a glorious boundary!
Quick single! On a length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari presses forward and taps it towards cover-point. Single taken!
Lovely delivery! Another loopy ball, full again, outside off. Virat Kohli leans to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Flatter now, on middle. Virat Kohli stays in his crease and pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller, outside off. Hanuma Vihari pushes it towards cover-point for a single.
Tosses it up, full again, on middle. Hanuma Vihari eases it to the fielder at mid off.
Slower through the air, spinning away, outside off. Hanuma Vihari leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, full, around off. Hanuma Vihari leans and blocks it out.
On the pads this time. Vihari easily flicks it to fine leg for a single.

Ohh..the angle from 'round the wicket nearly does the trick here! A good-length delivery from 'round the wicket, around off. Vihari looks to defend it but the ball straightens a bit after coming into him from the angle. It catches the outside edge of his blade. However, the ball falls short of the first slip fielder. The ball hits his finger and goes behind him for a couple.
Back of a length, on off. Vihari blocks it out this time.
Fullish delivery, outside off from 'round the wicket. Vihari drives it back to the bowler now.
FOUR! Vihari is looking quite comfortable here, he plays a lovely shot again! An overpitched delivery, outside off. Vihari gets a good stride forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
A full delivery on middle and leg. Vihari flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Vishwa Fernando comes back into the attack.
Again tossed up, outside off. Kohli pushes it towards covers now.

Ohh..in the air but safe! Tossed up on off and very slow in the air. Kohli tries to work it towards the leg side. However, he gets a leading edge and the ball goes towards deep extra-cover region for a couple.
Tossed up on middle. Kohli defends this off the front foot.
The crowd erupts as Virat Kohli walks out to bat on his 100th Test.

OUT! LBW! Lasith Embuldeniya strikes! He has been brilliant so far and is finally rewarded! Mayank Agarwal has to walk back and he will be disappointed but a very good delivery this! An arm ball this time on middle. Agarwal presses forward to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball hits him on the front pad. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Mayank Agarwal consults with Hanuma Vihari but they decide to not take a review and that is the second wicket for Sri Lanka.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Lasith Embuldeniya

Commentary.Commentary: Slower in the air, around off. Agarwal pushes it towards the off side.
Shorter on off this time. Agarwal goes back and punches it to covers. Dimuth Karunaratne does well to stop it this time.
Another back of a length delivery on middle. Vihari plays it calmly towards the leg side again.
Back of a length, on middle. Vihari defends it calmly towards the leg side.
A length delivery, on off. Vihari is compact in his defence again. It goes towards mid off but no single.
Shorter this time but down the leg side. Vihari looks to pull it but misses. The keeper does well to dive to his left and stop it.
Back of a length, on off at 148.7 kph. Vihari goes back and blocks it out.
A bouncer down the leg side this time. Vihari ducks under it.

Tries a quicker delivery this time and goes a fraction short around off. Vihari goes back and punches it through cover-point for three runs. Actually Dimuth Karunaratne misfields there as he slides to stop it and that allows them to take three runs.
Slower and tossed up around off. Vihari gets forward again and defends it.
Another lovely delivery. He is bowling on that tight line and the length that it making the batter play on the front foot. Vihari though does well to block it out.
Slower in the air, around off at 79.6 kph. Vihari gets forward and defends it towards the off side.
Slightly quicker this time, on off. Vihari blocks it out.
Nicely tossed up on off. Vihari defends this off the front foot.
A short delivery this time on middle. Agarwal ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle and leg at 143 kph. Vihari is hurried by that ball and manages to work it towards the leg side for a single.
On a length, around off. Vihari waits for it and then plays it late towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle and leg and this one nips back in sharply. Vihari looks to work it towards the leg side but misses and the ball hits him high on the pads.
On a length, around off at 141 kph. Agarwal pushes it towards point for a single.
Full delivery on off. Agarwal drives it to mid off. Better line from Kumara.
Tossed up on off. Agarwal drives it to long off for an easy single.
Loopy delivery on middle this time. Agarwal defends this off the front foot.
Slightly shorter outside off. Vihari cuts it to deep cover for a single.
Quicker on middle. This time Vihari blocks it out comfortably.
Slower in the air on middle. Vihari defends but gets the inside edge onto his pads. There is an appeal from the Lankan players but the inside-edge saves Vihari there.
Tossed up on off. Agarwal drives it to long off for a single.
A length delivery on middle. Agarwal clips it to deep square leg for a single. He needs to be around that off stump line.
Back of a length, around leg. Vihari glances it to fine leg for a single.
A good-length delivery, on off. Vihari just blocks it out.
On a length and around leg this time. Vihari looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits his pads but it is going down leg. Vihari misses out on a scoring opportunity there!
A fullish delivery around off. Agarwal leans forward and drives it through covers. The fielder there puts in a dive and saves a run for his team as the batters run three.
On a length and this one nips back into middle and leg. Agarwal defends this off the inside half of his blade to square leg.
Another lovely delivery! Tossed up outside off and turning away this time. Vihari gets forward and looks to push at it but gets beaten off the outside edge.
Nicely tossed up on middle this time. Vihari gets well forward and blocks it.
Again provides a bit of width and Agarwal goes deep in his crease again and cuts it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Slower in the air and slightly shorter with a bit of width outside off. Agarwal waits for it and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Slower in the air and outside off. Agarwal pushes it towards the off side.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Agarwal defends this off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.

DRINKS! The first hour has certainly belonged to India. They have been scoring quite freely here. But Sri Lanka have done well to break the opening partnership by getting the big wicket of Rohit Sharma. They need to capitalize on the same now. While India will be looking to build another partnership here with the pitch looking nice and flat. Also, it's time for some spin! Lasith Embuldeniya comes into the attack.
This time a pacy full delivery on middle at 147.2 kph. Vihari blocks it out towards the leg side.
The short-pitch stuff continues. It is down the leg side and Vihari just lets it go.
Another shorter length delivery around leg. Vihari lets it go and the keeper moves to his left and fails to collect it cleanly.
Bangs this short on middle at 147.3 kph. Vihari though ducks under it quite comfortably.
A length ball, on middle. Vihari blocks it out this time.

FOUR! Nice shot! Beautifully driven! A fullish delivery around off. Vihari drives as he takes a stride forward and creams it through covers for a boundary. Indian batters are enjoying some pace from Kumara.
Back of a length, on off at 122.9 kph. Vihari turns it towards mid-wicket for an easy single.
A length delivery and this time he corrects his line. Serves this on middle and Vihari blocks it out.
FOUR! So first boundary for Vihari but a poor line from Lakmal! A length delivery, drifting on the pads this time. Vihari clips it past square leg for a boundary. Easy pickings for him.
A length delivery, on off at 128.3 kph. Vihari is well forward this time and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Vihari plays back to this ball, it stays a tad low but Vihari manages to block it out.
On a good length, around off. Vihari presses forward and defends it solidly.

On a length, angling in, around off. Hanuma Vihari shuffles across, and he jabs his bat down, but the ball goes off the inside edge towards fine leg for a single. He gets off the mark! A successful over for Sri Lanka!
Hanuma Vihari walks in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lahiru Kumara draws first blood! He has been expensive but he has been rewarded now. He gets rid of Rohit Sharma. Lahiru Kumara set him up earlier with a few short balls and tempts him again to go after it, but Rohit Sharma holes out this time. Short, angling it in on middle. Rohit Sharma once again goes for the pull shot, this time he gets cramped for room and the ball goes off the top edge towards Suranga Lakmal at fine leg who takes a good catch. Sri Lanka have their first breakthrough.
Commentary.Howout: c Suranga Lakmal b Lahiru Kumara

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller now, around off. Rohit Sharma pushes it towards mid off.
FOUR! Another short ball and the result is the same! Fraction short though this time, around middle. Rohit Sharma stays back, and pulls it past mid-wicket for another boundary. 50 up for India!
FOUR! A short ball to Rohit Sharma will always be punished! Lahiru Kumara drops it short, around off. Rohit Sharma picks up the length and pulls it over mid-wicket for a cracking boundary.
Full in length, outside off, at 140.6 clicks. Rohit Sharma presses forward and defends it out.
Fullish again, around middle. Mayank Agarwal defends it towards mid off.
Swinging it in, on a length, around the pads. Mayank Agarwal works it away towards square leg for a couple of runs.
Tad fuller now, angling in, around off. Mayank Agarwal leans and defends it out.
Shaping back in, around the pads, on a length. Rohit Sharma tucks it towards deep square leg. Single taken!
Angling in, outside off, on a length. Rohit Sharma presses forward and leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Rohit Sharma offers no shot to that.
Yorker-length delivery, on middle. Mayank Agarwal digs it out towards cover. 9 runs off Lahiru Kumara's first over!
Back of a length, outside off. Rohit Sharma pushes it off the back foot towards deep cover for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Too full, wide of off. Rohit Sharma leans, opens the face of the bat, and carves it past cover for a boundary.
Angling in, around middle and off, on a length. Rohit Sharma pushes it towards mid on.
So here is the first bowling change of this Test match. Lahiru Kumara comes into the attack now. He replaces Vishwa Fernando.
FOUR! Welcome to the attack, Lahiru Kumara! A full toss, around middle and leg. Rohit Sharma clips it past mid on for a boundary.
Outside off, on a length. Mayank Agarwal pushes it towards cover.
Length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal taps it towards gully. Pathum Nissanka there dives to his right and makes a good stop. Saved a certain boundary there!
Back of a length, swinging it in, around off. Mayank Agarwal blocks it out.
Fraction shorter now, around middle. Mayank Agarwal pulls it gently past mid-wicket for a brace. Suranga Lakmal has overstepped here and the umpire signals a no ball!
Good-length delivery, angling in around middle, at 127.4 clicks. Mayank Agarwal blocks it towards gully.
Back of a length, around off. Rohit Sharma taps it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Angling in around middle and off. Rohit Sharma defends it out.
Length ball, around the fifth stump line. Mayank Agarwal blocks it out.
Shaping away, on a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend this off the back foot, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Classy! Fuller ball again, ouside off. Mayank Agarwal presses forward, presents the full face of the ball, and pushes it past mid off for a beautiful boundary.
Touch fuller, around off. Mayank Agarwal blocks it towards cover-point.
On a length, outside off. Rohit Sharma taps it towards cover and scampers through to the other end for a quick single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma defends it towards mid off.
On a length, sliding down leg. Mayank Agarwal misses his flick.
Length, around middle. Mayank Agarwal blocks it out.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Fullish delivery, around off. Mayank Agarwal leans to block this but gets an outside edge left of the diving gully fielder. The ball races away towards the third man fence for a boundary.
No ball! Good-length delivery, outside off. Mayank Agarwal taps it towards point. Suranga Lakmal has overstepped here and a no ball is called!
Well bowled! On a length, outside off, at around 129 clicks. Mayank Agarwal presses forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Angling in again, on a length, around middle and leg, at 127.6 clicks, Mayank Agarwal taps it towards square leg.
Angling in, on middle, on a fuller length. Mayank Agarwal blocks it out.
Shaping away, outside off, on a length. Rohit Sharma taps it towards point. 13 runs off the over!
FOUR! Glorious! Full-length delivery, outside off. Rohit Sharma leans, opens the face of his bat, and drives it past gully for a boundary. Third boundary of the over!
Length ball, around middle. Rohit Sharma blocks it out.
Much fuller now, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leans to drive but gets an inside edge towards fine leg. Single taken!
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Fraction short again, outside off. Mayank Agarwal stays in his crease, opens the face of the bat, and guides it past point for a boundary.
FOUR! Mayank Agarwal gets off the mark in style! Vishwa Fernando drops it short, outside off. Mayank Agarwal gets on his toes and pushes it past cover for a boundary.
Length, outside off. Rohit Sharma pushes it towards cover. No run there!
An inswinger now, outside off, on a length. Rohit Sharma leaves it alone.
FOUR! First boundary for Rohit Sharma and India! Perfect timing on this occasion! Touch fuller, darting it around the pads. Rohit Sharma uses his wrists and flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Rohit Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket.
Lenth ball, around the pads. Rohit Sharma once again looks to clip this on the leg side but gets an outside edge towards the fielder at gully, who once again, collects it on the bounce.
Extra bounce! Fraction shorter, around middle and leg. Rohit Sharma looks to flick it on the leg side, but the ball goes off the leading edge towards gully, who collects it on a couple of bounces.
Swing and a miss! Forcing the batter to dive this time! Tad fuller, shaping away, outside off at 136.2 clicks. Mayank Agarwal leans and looks to drive but misses.
Good-length delivery, around off. Mayank Agarwal leans and blocks it out.
An outswinger this time, on a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets that go through.
Swinging it in, around middle, on a length. Mayank Agarwal tries to defend but gets an inside edge through his legs towards short fine leg.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Rohit Sharma opens the face of the bat and pushes it towards cover for a single. Rohit Sharma and India are up and running!
Vishwa Fernando begins with a tad fuller ball, nipping in, around middle. Rohit Sharma looks to block this but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Good ball to begin with for Vishwa Fernando!
Vishwa Fernando will share the new ball with Suranga Lakmal.
Another length delivery, shaping away, around off. Mayank Agarwal stays in his crease and blocks it out watchfully. A maiden to begin with!
An outswinger, outside off, on a length, at 129.1 clicks. Mayank Agarwal shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Beaten! A beautiful delivery! On a length, an outswinger, outside off. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Another good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Mayank Agarwal looks to block this but gets a bottom edge towards third slip, who collects it on the bounce.
Suranga Lakmal begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Mayank Agarwal blocks it out.

Sri Lankan players are out there in the middle as they take their respective field positions. Rohit Sharma and Mayank Agarwal are the openers for India and they walk out to the middle now. Suranga Lakmal to start with the ball for Sri Lanka. Mayank Agarwal will be on strike. Here we go...

All the players are out in the middle for their respective national anthem. It will be Sri Lanka's national anthem followed by India's. We are done with the anthems and it is time for action to begin now!

Virat Kohli is being felicitated for his 100th Test. A proud moment for Virat Kohli, as he receives a special cap from his childhood hero, Rahul Dravid! Virat Kohli says that it's a special moment for him, and he thanks all his teammates and family for their support. States that in today's generation they play a lot of cricket with all the formats of the game, but he is feeling proud to play his 100 games in the purest format of the game and receive his 100th Test cap from his childhood hero, Rahul Dravid.

Dimuth Karunaratne, the skipper of Sri Lanka says that they would have batted first as well, they are playing with 3 seamers, but the wicket looks good to bat on. Mentions that they have played 300 tests but they have never won in India, but they want to create history here and do something different today. Informs that they are playing with 3 seamers and 2 spinners.

Rohit Sharma, the skipper of India, says that they will bat first. He says that it is similar Indian condition and it is important to score big while batting first. He says that it is a big opportunity for him to lead the Test team and he never dreamt of it but would like to do well here. He mentions that there has been a buzz around the team and says that this is a special occasion for Virat and everyone and they are looking forward to this game. Mentions that they are playing with three spinners and two seamers.

Sri Lanka (Playing XI) - Dimuth Karunaratne (C), Lahiru Thirimanne, Pathum Nissanka, Charith Asalanka, Dhananjaya de Silva, Angelo Mathews, Niroshan Dickwella (WK), Lasith Embuldeniya, Suranga Lakmal, Vishwa Fernando, Lahiru Kumara.
India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma (C), Mayank Agarwal, Hanuma Vihari, Virat Kohli, Shreyas Iyer, Rishabh Pant (WK), Ravindra Jadeja, Ravichandran Ashwin, Jayant Yadav, Mohammed Shami, Jasprit Bumrah.
TOSS - India have won the toss and they have elected to BAT first.

PITCH REPORT - Deep Dasgupta and Russel Arnold are down near the pitch. Russel says it looks different and it looks like a batting track but a deeper look will show some cracks but they are not likely to break. He mentions that there is grass in the back of a length area of the pitch and there will be help for spinners as well. Both Deep and Russel mention that the team winning the toss should bat first.

It’s a new and fresh start for India in the longest format of the game, as Rohit Sharma is all set to take over the Test captaincy. India have roped in some young and talented players as well after players like Ajinkya Rahane, Cheteshwar Pujara, and Ishant Sharma were left out. This will also be Virat Kohli's 100th Test and he will be eager to score big on this special occasion. A lot to look forward to in this match. Who will dominate Day 1 of this Test? We will find out. Stay tuned for the Toss and team news.

Sri Lanka have not been at their best in Test cricket in India. But they are well and truly capable of changing things around. Skipper, Dimuth Karunaratne and Lasith Embuldeniya are the players who have displayed their magic in Test cricket and they will be the ones to watch out for. The visitors will have to get their best game forward and prove their worth against India.

Hello and welcome folks! It’s time for the first Test between India and Sri Lanka to get underway! After an exciting T20I series, it’s time for some red-ball cricket. India will be high on confidence coming into this game after a dominant performance in the shortest format. Although their last Test series against South Africa did not go their way, they will be eager to get back to winning ways in the longest format. While Sri Lanka will have to leave their white-ball woes behind them and start fresh in Test cricket. Both these sides have quality in their ranks and we can expect a cracker of a game. Not to forget, the first Test will be the 100th Test of one of the greatest players, Virat Kohli, thus making this a special game.
... FIRST TEST ...

Indian players are out there in the middle again for the second innings. Sri Lankan openers, Dimuth Karunaratne and Lahiru Thirimanne are the openers for Sri Lanka. Mohammed Shami to start with the ball for India. Here we go...

India have enforced the follow-on! How often we have seen this happening to the visiting teams in India. India puts a big first innings score on the board and then the visiting team just crumbles under the pressure against a quality Indian bowling attack. The spinners were always going to be the threat for Lanka but credit should be given to Shami and Bumrah too as they bowled their heart out and got important breakthroughs. Ashwin and Jadeja did what they have been doing for many years now and completely bamboozled the Sri Lankan batting lineup. Jadeja finished with a five-wicket haul in addition to his superb 175 with the bat and India are right on the top in this game now. India have enforced a follow on. Sri Lanka, on the other hand, will be mighty disappointed with their performance with the bat. It was always going to be a tough task for them but they would have hoped for a better performance here. The opening partnership started solidly though but once they departed the floodgates opened. There was a decent partnership between Nissanka and Charith Asalanka but once Charith Asalanka departed things started falling apart and eventually Sri Lanka bundled out for 174 giving away a lead of 400 runs to India. A tough test awaits Sri Lanka in their second innings.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Ravindra Jadeja gets his five-wicket haul! What a Test match he is having! Ravindra Jadeja keeps it simple, tad quicker, attacking the stumps. Lahiru Kumara looks to defend this without any foot movement, and the ball goes past his outside edge and knocks the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja will be on a hat-trick in the next innings! Sri Lanka are bundled out for 174! India have a lead of 400.
Commentary.Howout: b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary.Commentary: Lahiru Kumara is the last man in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Ravindra Jadeja is now one away from his five-wicket haul. A loopy ball, turning away a tad around middle. Vishwa Fernando leans to defend this, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards Rohit Sharma at second slip who pouches it safely. Wickets continue to tumble and Sri Lanka are now 9 down!
Commentary.Howout: c Rohit Sharma b Ravindra Jadeja

Commentary.Commentary: Loopy ball, around middle. Vishwa Fernando blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle. Pathum Nissanka pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Shorter ball, around off. Pathum Nissanka defends it towards mid off.
Fuller in length, around off. Pathum Nissanka steps down and pushes it to cover.
Shorter ball, around middle. Vishwa Fernando ducks under it.
On a length, outside off. Vishwa Fernando leaves it alone.
Fuller now, around off. Vishwa Fernando blocks it out.
Vishwa Fernando is the next man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! India are all over Sri Lanka! Mohammed Shami comes into the attack and strikes! Shami drops it short now, around middle. Lasith Embuldeniya looks to back away and ducks, but leaves his bat hanging. The ball goes off the top of the bat and lobs behind the short leg fielder. Mayank Agarwal has plenty of time to go back and take an easy catch. Sri Lanka are now 8 down!
Commentary.Howout: c Mayank Agarwal b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Tad fuller, outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya leans to defend but the ball goes off the outside towards second slip, who collects it on the bounce.
Good-length delivery, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya blocks it off the front foot.
Tosses it up, full in length, around off. Pathum Nissanka leans and blocks it out.
Loopy ball, full and around off. Pathum Nissanka defends it out.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Full again, on middle. Pathum Nissanka gets down on his knee and swipes this uppishly towards deep square leg for another boundary.
FOUR! Fuller ball, on middle. Pathum Nissanka gets low and sweeps it with inner half of his bat towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Flatter, on middle and full in length. Pathum Nissanka steps down and pushes it towards mid off.

ICC WOMEN'S CRICKET WORLD CUP UPDATE- Meanwhile, India Women are reeling at 134/6 after 37 overs against Pakistan Women in their opening World Cup game. Sir  Ravindra Jadeja was the stand-out player for India, he scored an unbeaten 175 and guided India to a total of 574. After a scintillating batting performance, India continued their dominance with the ball and sent back four Sri Lankan batters. They will be hoping they can grab early wickets in the first session and put the visitors under immense pressure. While Sri Lanka will need a big partnership to get them out of trouble. Pathum Nissanka and Charith Asalanka are the players who will resume their batting and will want to remain at the crease and give a tough fight. An interesting first session coming up. Stay tuned.

Welcome back, folks! We are now into Day 3 of this exciting Test between India and Sri Lanka. We witnessed an entertaining second day of this Test with India ending the day in a commanding position. The visitors might be on the back foot but they are not out of the game just yet, they will be coming into Day 3 hoping they can put up a healthy partnership. Although it’s only going to get tougher for them as we can expect the ball to turn more on this pitch. Another thrilling day of Test cricket awaits us.
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 ...

Right then, that is all we have from Day 2 of this Test match! India have dominated Day 2 and it will be interesting to see if Lankan Lions can fight their way back into this game on Day 3. The first ball will be bowled at 9.30 am IST (4.00 am GMT). Our coverage, as you know, will start well in advance. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Ravindra Jadeja, the star of the day is down for the chat. He says that he is feeling very good. Mentions that on Day 1, Pant was taking the bowlers on, and he was just enjoying his batting from the other end. States that he was staying calm in the middle, and he was just trying to build a partnership. Informs that he always enjoys batting and bowling with Ashwin. Adds that as the game progresses the ball might turn more.

Sri Lanka were pretty flat with the ball earlier in the day and that made life difficult for their batters in this final session. The quality of the Indian bowling attack challenged them regularly, though Sri Lankan openers showed a great fight starting off in a solid manner, they could not carry on and eventually perished. Sri Lanka lost four wickets at the end and that will hurt them going into Day 3. Skipper, Dimuth Karunaratne and Mathews were looking quite good while they were in the middle but with both the senior batters back into the hut, now it is upto the young guns from Sri Lanka to bail them out. Overall, a perfect day for India and Sri Lanka would need a lot of things to go their way on Day 3 to stay in this game.

Indian bowlers had a luxury of a big score under their belt. However, they still needed to bowl well to put pressure on the opposition's batting lineup and Indian bowlers showed their class yet again. The pitch had some help for the bowlers but not much. However, all the bowlers showed tremendous discipline and fire to put pressure on the Lankan batters on a consistent basis. Ashwin broke the opening stand and after that, Jadeja and Bumrah with their superb spell put the pressure on, and eventually, India got four wickets in the session. Especially the wicket of Mathews was key and it is going to be a tough task for the Lankans on Day 3 against a quality Indian bowling attack. Earlier, the foundation was led by the batters with Jadeja smashing a career-best 175 to take India to a big total and that meant that Sri Lanka were always behind the 8-ball coming into this final session.

This has been a pretty intense session of Test cricket! India came hard at Sri Lanka throughout the session but Lankans were also upto the task and fought with great character for the most part of this session. However, they lost four wickets in this session as the quality of Indian bowlers finally got the better of them and with a trail of 466, India are in a driver’s seat at the end of Day 2. Sri Lanka need a pretty special effort on Day 3 to stop India here. The late Shane Warne has called Jadeja a 'Rockstar' during Jadeja's early days and he has surely given a fitting tribute to the great spinner with his superb all-round performance on Day 2.

India have dominated this Test match and they will be hoping to put another strong performance in the second Test which will be a day-night affair. That Test will start at 2.00 pm IST (8.30 am GMT) on Saturday, March 12 at Bengaluru. As you know our coverage will start well in advance. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Ravindra Jadeja is the Player of the Match. He says that Mohali is his lucky ground and whenever he comes to Mohali, he gets positive vibes. On being asked about his batting, he states that he wanted to build a partnership with Pant, but he was standing at the other end and enjoying his batting. Informs that he does not know anything about stats but he is happy to score runs and pick up wickets, which gives him some confidence. States that he has done nothing different, he just backed his instincts, he looks to keep things simple. Concludes by saying that he has never played with the pink ball before, but he will practice before the game and he is sure he will be comfortable with the ball.

Rohit Sharma, the skipper of India, says that it was a great performance and they have ticked all the boxes and he is happy with the performance. He mentions that he did not think that it will be a hree days Test match because the pitch was good to bat on but credits his bowlers for applying pressure and they were great.  He states that these are good signs for Indian cricket and it was a landmark Test match for Virat. He mentions that they first wanted to win this Test match and it is heartening to see all big performances. He adds that they wanted to give Jayant some overs and give him some confidence as he is the third spinner in the team. He says that it has been a great performance by Jadeja and he mentions that the pink-ball Test match will be a big challenge and looking forward to it. He mentions that it will be a challenge as it is their only second pink-ball Test match at home and says that he is looking forward to how the pitch behaves there and then take it from there.

Dimuth Karunaratne, the skipper of Sri Lanka, says that the batters need to put their hands up, it was easy to bat on this track, but they had to get a big score. Mentions that they thought the pitch was going to be up and down and cracks would open and that's why they played three seamers, but they should have still bowled better and restricted India. Informs that they were either very defensive or they were aggressive, but they need to rotate the strike and bat better. Concludes that, the batters will have to step up and score big, and they will come back stronger in the next game.
Stay tuned for the presentation.

Ravichandran Ashwin is down for a chat. On being asked about Jadeja's batting, he says that Jadeja has come a really long way in the last four-five years, and he thinks that Jadeja's batting has gone one notch higher! States that Jadeja and he realized that Jayant has not bowled a lot and he being the third spinner he had to get a few overs in the middle. Informs that he wanted to bat well, and since he had four weeks off he did change a few things in his batting and he was trying to apply those in this match, but he was staying positive. Adds that the surface was a good one, Jadeja and he were trying hard to get wickets, but it was tough to get the batsmen out when they were very defensive and says that they cannot keep Bumrah and Shami out of it, they bowled well and put pressure!

Sri Lanka have a lot to ponder about, right from their tactics to go with only one frontline spinner on this track and their execution of skills in the middle. They were laid low by the injury to Lahiru Kumara on the first day of the Test itself and eventually gave away 574 runs with the ball. It was always going to be tough after that but being a subcontinent team Lankans were expected to play spin better and show some application. However, they were quite poor with the bat in both the innings and Nissanka in the first innings and Dickwella in the second innings were only the two batters who showed some resilience out there. They need their senior batters like Angelo Mathews and skipper, Dimuth Karunaratne to step up otherwise another tough Test awaits them in a couple of days' time.

A classical Indian Test victory at home. India piling on a big score in the first innings and then putting the opposition team under pressure with spin playing the major role. The game was probably over in the first session of Day 3 when India picked up seven wickets to demolish any hopes Sri Lanka had coming into Day 3. Then, the caravan continued and with six more wickets in the final session, India bowled out Sri Lanka twice in this Test match with ease. Ashwin and Jadeja were brilliant with the ball as usual but there were important contributions by the seamers and that makes this bowling performance even sweeter. The foundation was laid by the batting unit earlier in the game with Jadeja notching up his career-best score and almost all other batters making decent contributions. Overall, India have done what everyone expects them to do in home conditions and they will be looking to continue their dominance in the second Test match.

India have demolished Sri Lanka by a huge margin of an innings and 222 runs in this first Test match and Rohit Sharma begins his Test captaincy journey with a commanding victory. India were always expected to win this Test match but the sheer dominance and the fact that they clinched this inside three days is quite an achievement. If you have seen at least some part of this game in the last two days, you will know that Sir Jadeja has been a standout performer in this Test match. He has taken 9 wickets in this Test match and scored a mammoth 175 with the bat. Overall, India have outplayed Sri Lanka in all facets of the game and Sri Lanka need to be much better in the second Test if they want to challenge India in that Test match.

ICC WOMEN'S CRICKET WORLD CUP UPDATE - India Women are in a commanding position for now. After 25 overs Pakistan Women have scored 78 runs but have lost five wickets. They need 167 more runs from the remaining 25 overs. India's veteran bowler Jhulan Goswami has grabbed two wickets and has been very economical as well so far. A good chance for India Women to begin their World Cup campaign with a victory.

The first hour of the session, Sri Lanka did show some grit and determination, with Nissanka and Asalanka scoring runs. But once Asalanka perished, wickets just started to tumble for them. While Nissanka scored a half-century but he was stranded at the other end. He was the lone warrior for Sri Lanka, but he had no partners with him. They have lost one wicket already while following-on and they need a special effort to save this Test match now. A disappointing session for Sri Lanka and let's see how things pan out in the afternoon session. The post-Lunch session begins at 12.10 pm IST (6.40 am GMT). Stay tuned.

What a session this has been for India! They have taken 7 wickets and are bossing this game now with just 9 Sri Lankan wickets remaining and Lankans are still 390 runs behind. The session started with Nissanka and Charith Asalanka notching up a fifty partnership and it was all looking stable for Sri Lanka. However, the loss of Charith Asalanka's wicket created panic, and the Sri Lankan batting line-up just crumbled. Indian bowlers were fantastic with both spinners and seamers bowling brilliantly in the tandem and with Sir Jadeja taking a five-wicket-haul India ended with a 400 run lead in the first innings. Then, it was a brief period before Lunch that Lankan batters had to negotiate but Lahiru Thirimanne departed early and India would look to continue their domination in the afternoon session.
